      {
        "step_number": 4,
        "component_ref": null,
        "instruction": "Heat oil to 350F. Using a jhara drop the batter on the hot oil. Fry for 3-4 minutes and drop them in the sugar syrup. Do not crowd the oil. Rinse and dry the jhara between every batch. If the droplets are creatging tails, the batter is too thick, add few drops of water and try again. Of the bondes are becoming flat, the batter is too thin, add bit of besan and try again.",
